  "original_title": "\u0b92\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd: \u0b9a\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Country will perish if not united: Sajid",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Leader of the Opposition Sajith Premadasa said that in the last 3 years, the rulers of this country did not listen to what others said and acted thinking that they were right, and as a result, the country has fallen into a great abyss today.",
        "The leader of the opposition said that the country can be built through social reform that does not act in a dictatorial manner and listens to everyone's opinions, and for that he will listen to the proposals and ideas of the progressive parties and said that our aim is to rebuild the country.",
        "The Leader of the Opposition has stated that through a common national agenda that can unite diverse ideas, we can regain everything that our people have lost, and that he is ready to regain the breath that the people have lost, and pointed out that all sides should join hands in this effort.",
        "A meeting of the \"National Reforms and Forward Journey\" program for nation building was held yesterday (04) at the office of the Leader of the Opposition in Colombo.",
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena, Leader of Opposition Sajith Premadasa, United People's Shakti General Secretary Ranjith Mathuma Bandara, Members of Parliament Sarath Fonseka, Rajitha Senaratne, Mano Ganesan, Raoob Hakeem, C. Wigneswaran, P. Digambaram and some civil activists including Victor Ivan, Janaranjana, Kamini Vyankoda, Rohan Samarajeeva also participated in the event."
      ],
